input_data1 = np.random.random_sample([2, 4])
input_data2 = np.random.random_sample([2, 4])
input1 = Input((4,))
input2 = Input((4,))
out1 = Dense(4)(input1)
out2 = Dense(4)(input2)
from keras.engine import merge
m = merge([out1, out2], mode='cos', dot_axes=1)
kmodel = Model(input=[input1, input2], output=m)
self.modelTest([input_data1, input_data2], kmodel, random_weights=False,
    dump_weights=True, is_training=False)
